  "response_text": "Sure! Below is a sample weekly meal and fitness plan designed for general health and fitness. Adjust portion sizes according to your specific caloric needs, dietary restrictions, and fitness goals.\n\n### Weekly Meal Plan\n\n#### **Day 1: Monday**\n- **Breakfast:** Oatmeal with sliced banana and a sprinkle of cinnamon\n- **Snack:** Greek yogurt with honey and almonds\n- **Lunch:** Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, and balsamic vinaigrette\n- **Snack:** Carrot sticks with hummus\n- **Dinner:** Baked salmon, quinoa, and steamed broccoli\n\n#### **Day 2: Tuesday**\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie with spinach, banana, protein powder, and almond milk\n- **Snack:** Apple slices with peanut butter\n- **Lunch:** Turkey and avocado wrap with whole grain tortilla and side of mixed fruit\n- **Snack:** Mixed nuts\n- **Dinner:** Stir-fried tofu with mixed vegetables over brown rice\n\n#### **Day 3: Wednesday**\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs with spinach and whole-grain toast\n- **Snack:** Cottage cheese with pineapple\n- **Lunch:** Quinoa bowl with black beans, corn, diced tomatoes, and avocado\n- **Snack:** Celery sticks with cream cheese\n- **Dinner:** Grilled shrimp, zoodles (zucchini noodles), and marinara sauce\n\n#### **Day 4: Thursday**\n- **Breakfast:** Chia seed pudding with almond milk, topped with berries\n- **Snack:** Hard-boiled eggs\n- **Lunch:** Lentil soup with a side salad\n- **Snack:** Rice cakes with almond butter\n- **Dinner:** Chicken stir-fry with broccoli, bell peppers, and brown rice\n\n#### **Day 5: Friday**\n- **Breakfast:** Whole grain pancakes topped with fresh fruit\n- **Snack:** Smoothie with mixed berries and yogurt\n- **Lunch:** Grilled vegetable sandwich on whole grain bread\n- **Snack:** Popcorn (air-popped)\n- **Dinner:** Baked cod with sweet potato and asparagus\n\n#### **Day 6: Saturday**\n- **Breakfast:** Avocado toast with poached egg\n- **Snack:** Sliced cucumber with tzatziki\n- **Lunch:** Spinach and feta stuffed chicken breast with a side of roasted vegetables\n- **Snack:** Trail mix\n- **Dinner:** Veggie pizza on whole wheat crust\n\n#### **Day 7: Sunday**\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie bowl topped with granola and fruit\n- **Snack:** Bell pepper slices with guacamole\n- **Lunch:** Quinoa salad with chickpeas, cucumber, and feta\n- **Snack:** Dark chocolate square (70% or higher)\n- **Dinner:** Grilled steak with mixed greens and baked sweet potato\n\n### Weekly Fitness Plan\n\n#### **Day 1: Monday**\n- **Workout:** Full-body strength training (45 minutes)\n  - Squats, lunges, push-ups, rows, and planks\n- **Cool Down:** Stretching (15 minutes)\n\n#### **Day 2: Tuesday**\n- **Workout:** Cardio (30–45 minutes)\n  - Jogging, cycling, or interval training\n- **Core Workout:** Plank variations (15 minutes)\n\n#### **Day 3: Wednesday**\n- **Workout:** Yoga or Pilates (60 minutes)\n- **Cool Down:** Meditation or stretching (10 minutes)\n\n#### **Day 4: Thursday**\n- **Workout:** Upper body strength training (45 minutes)\n  - Dumbbell presses, bicep curls, tricep dips, shoulder raises\n- **Cool Down:** Stretching (15 minutes)\n\n#### **Day 5: Friday**\n- **Workout:** HIIT (High-Intensity Interval Training) (30 minutes)\n  - Short bursts of intense exercise followed by rest (e.g., burpees, jumping jacks, mountain climbers)\n- **Cool Down:** Stretching (15 minutes)\n\n#### **Day 6: Saturday**\n- **Workout:** Outdoor activity (hiking, cycling, or playing a sport) (60 minutes)\n- **Cool Down:** Stretching (10 minutes)\n\n#### **Day 7: Sunday**\n- **Rest Day:** Light activity (walking, gentle yoga) and focus on recovery.\n\n### Tips\n- Hydrate: Drink plenty of water throughout the day.\n- Sleep: Aim for 7–9 hours of quality sleep each night.\n- Adjust: Listen to your body and adjust workouts and meals as needed.\n- Variety: Feel free to swap similar meals or snacks based on your preferences.\n- Consult: If you have specific dietary needs or fitness goals, consider consulting a nutritionist or personal trainer.\n\nEnjoy your week of healthy eating and fitness!",
